President Donald J. Trump spoke with President Moon Jae-in of South Korea to discuss recent developments on the Korean Peninsula. They agreed to continue putting maximum pressure on North Korea and to avoid repeating past mistakes. Both countries are committed to ensuring a safe and successful 2018 Winter Olympic Games in Pyeongchang, and the United States will send a high-level delegation to the Olympics. They also agreed to coordinate the Olympics with military exercises to ensure the security of the Games.